definition: to meet with luck/to hand over for transportation/to check (one's baggage at an airport etc)
to hand over/to deliver/to pay (money)/to turn over/to make friends/to intersect (lines)/variant of 跤[jiao1]

sentences.english: What do you mean Iam lucky?
sentences.chinese: 你说我交运是什么旨趣？

sentences.english: The goods of your order are being manufactured for shipment.
sentences.chinese: 贵方订购的产品正准备交运中。

sentences.english: You must check your luggage in before noon.
sentences.chinese: 你必须在中午以前将行李交运。

sentences.english: Support effectiveness evaluation for transportation equipment is the base of the optimization of military transportation system.
sentences.chinese: 运输装备保障效能评估是军交运输系统优化的基础。

sentences.english: We hope to get a commitment from the manufacturer to deliver the parts on time.
sentences.chinese: 我们希望生产者能允诺准时交运零件。

sentences.english: The goods have to be delivered by the end of June.
sentences.chinese: 货物必须在六月底前交运。

sentences.english: Would you please check if the shipment has been made?
sentences.chinese: 请你检查一下，看是否已经交运了，好吗？
